Package: MIMsim
Type: Package
Title: Mixed inheritance model simulation of disease within family studies
Version: 0.1
Date: 2015-10-14
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alexandra", "Gillett", email = "alexandra.a.gillett@kcl.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Ammar", "Al-Chalabi",role = "aut"),
    person(c("Cathryn", "M"), "Lewis", role = "aut"))
Depends:
    R (>= 2.14.1)
Imports:
    methods,
    data.table,
    plyr,
    kinship2
Description: A package for simulating data from family studies of disease risk.
    Disease is modelled using a mixed inheritance model. Simulated pedigrees are
    bi-linear and span 3 or 4 generations. The ascertainment of families can be
    influenced by the family history of disease, allowing users of MIMsim to explore
    the effect of ascertainment bias within family studies of disease risk and
    penetrance.
Author: Alexandra Gillett [aut, cre],
    Ammar Al-Chalabi [aut],
    Cathryn M Lewis [aut]
Maintainer: Alexandra Gillett <alexandra.a.gillett@kcl.ac.uk>
